Honor rediviuus [sic] or An analysis of honor and armory. by Matt: Carter Esq. Honor redivivus. Carter, Matthew, fl. 1660. Gaywood, Richard, fl. 1650-1680, engraver.
[10], 256, 247-251, [1] p., [8] leaves of plates : coats of arms (woodcuts)
printed for Henry Herringman 1660 and are to be sould by Henry Herringman at the Ancker on the lowest side of the New-Exchange, London : [1660]
The title page is engraved and signed "R. Gaywood fecit"; the plate is an altered version of the one first used in Wing C658. With two handwritten pages at end. Annotation on Thomason copy: "June". Reproduction of the original in the British Library.
